00:08:56.900 --> 00:08:59.570
OAuth is an authentication
mechanism.

00:08:59.570 --> 00:09:01.520
And for the Mirror API,
it's analogous

00:09:01.520 --> 00:09:02.980
to the install process.

00:09:02.980 --> 00:09:06.660
The user gives permission to
the Glass service to write

00:09:06.660 --> 00:09:10.080
into their timeline
and get updates.

00:09:10.080 --> 00:09:13.440
JSON is the encoding, JavaScript
Object Notation.

00:09:13.440 --> 00:09:17.730
It's pretty much the language
that we send over REST, which

00:09:17.730 --> 00:09:18.830
is the protocol.

00:09:18.830 --> 00:09:20.930
And that's just HTTP.

00:09:20.930 --> 00:09:23.200
It's like submitting a web form,
but in the background.

00:09:26.330 --> 00:09:28.730
And all that work happens
right here.

00:09:28.730 --> 00:09:31.190
And this is what I think is
really key about the Mirror

00:09:31.190 --> 00:09:35.240
API is that it's super simple
to develop for, and yet you

00:09:35.240 --> 00:09:37.720
could also build powerful
services.

00:09:37.720 --> 00:09:40.690
All your work is going to be
right here between your

00:09:40.690 --> 00:09:42.390
service and Google.

00:09:42.390 --> 00:09:46.200
And then Google handles the sync
to Glass, dealing with

00:09:46.200 --> 00:09:49.650
any connectivity issues and
actually rendering things on

00:09:49.650 --> 00:09:51.005
the client on Glass.

