00:37:59.030 --> 00:38:04.010
Twitter and Glass, they just
work so well together.

00:38:04.010 --> 00:38:05.330
There's a bunch of stuff
that you can do

00:38:05.330 --> 00:38:06.840
with the Twitter Glassware.

00:38:06.840 --> 00:38:08.905
You can get tweets from
plus mentions.

00:38:11.770 --> 00:38:15.990
You get the tweets that you
have mobile notifications

00:38:15.990 --> 00:38:17.320
turned on for.

00:38:17.320 --> 00:38:19.820
So if I have mobile
notifications turned on for my

00:38:19.820 --> 00:38:23.860
friend, Sydney, as he tweets,
I get those on Glass.

00:38:23.860 --> 00:38:25.432
You get direct messages,
and you can

00:38:25.432 --> 00:38:28.190
respond to those messages.

00:38:28.190 --> 00:38:29.900
And you can share
a picture from

00:38:29.900 --> 00:38:31.120
Glass directly to Twitter.

00:38:31.120 --> 00:38:32.710
And it'll post it as
a photo tweet.

00:38:35.810 --> 00:38:37.695
A tweet on Glass looks
a bit like this.

00:38:37.695 --> 00:38:42.570
As you know, our friends from
NASA just returned to Earth.

00:38:42.570 --> 00:38:45.840
And it was really fun watching
all of their updates getting

00:38:45.840 --> 00:38:48.280
retweeted by NASA astronauts
and getting that on Glass

00:38:48.280 --> 00:38:49.440
throughout the day.

00:38:49.440 --> 00:38:52.700
Because they're updating about
their return and their tests

00:38:52.700 --> 00:38:55.940
and seeing their family.

00:38:55.940 --> 00:38:59.320
And if I want, I can reply to
these tweets, I can retweet,

00:38:59.320 --> 00:39:03.370
and I can favorite
right from Glass.

00:39:03.370 --> 00:39:04.520
Super simple.

00:39:04.520 --> 00:39:07.520
And because Twitter is that
short message model, it just

00:39:07.520 --> 00:39:10.840
makes a lot of sense on Glass.

00:39:10.840 --> 00:39:12.510
Another thing that I really
love about the Twitter

00:39:12.510 --> 00:39:15.215
Glassware is this direct
messaging capability.

00:39:15.215 --> 00:39:19.390
Now here Alain sent me a DM
asking if I was ready for the

00:39:19.390 --> 00:39:20.640
afters hour party.

00:39:23.040 --> 00:39:24.590
To which I replied,
most certainly.

00:39:24.590 --> 00:39:25.605
Because of course I was.

00:39:25.605 --> 00:39:27.366
It was awesome, right?

00:39:27.366 --> 00:39:27.760
Yeah.

00:39:27.760 --> 00:39:29.180
It was a good party.

00:39:29.180 --> 00:39:32.670
I think that might be the
best I/O party yet.

00:39:32.670 --> 00:39:34.860
Anyway, I hit Reply.

00:39:34.860 --> 00:39:36.330
I saved that message.

00:39:36.330 --> 00:39:40.060
And that gets added to
the thread on Glass.

00:39:40.060 --> 00:39:42.980
Remember, I talked about these
bundles and threaded bundles?

00:39:42.980 --> 00:39:46.890
All Twitter had to do was insert
one more item, set the

00:39:46.890 --> 00:39:51.020
bundle ID for that bundle--
which is any arbitrary string

00:39:51.020 --> 00:39:51.810
it decides.

00:39:51.810 --> 00:39:54.180
Maybe it's an internal
representation of this

00:39:54.180 --> 00:39:56.240
conversation--

00:39:56.240 --> 00:39:58.460
and that bundle grows.

00:39:58.460 --> 00:40:01.660
And it keeps growing as
we reply back and

00:40:01.660 --> 00:40:04.550
forth to each other.

00:40:04.550 --> 00:40:06.435
It's pretty neat, huh?

00:40:06.435 --> 00:40:07.740
All right.

00:40:07.740 --> 00:40:08.990
Let's talk about Evernote.

00:40:14.590 --> 00:40:17.720
Evernote, as you know, is
great for taking notes,

00:40:17.720 --> 00:40:20.750
capturing ideas and experiences,
and collaborating

00:40:20.750 --> 00:40:23.120
with your friends.

00:40:23.120 --> 00:40:26.600
One of the things that I do,
one of my patterns with

00:40:26.600 --> 00:40:28.610
Evernote, is I'll take
notes and then I'll

00:40:28.610 --> 00:40:29.780
reference those notes.

00:40:29.780 --> 00:40:33.230
I do shopping lists all the time
on Evernote, my common

00:40:33.230 --> 00:40:34.330
shopping list every week.

00:40:34.330 --> 00:40:35.815
And then I add items,
remove items.

00:40:35.815 --> 00:40:38.340
And then I'm in the store, and
I have my phone out, and I'm

00:40:38.340 --> 00:40:39.780
looking at that shopping list.

00:40:39.780 --> 00:40:42.650
And it's much cooler having
that experience on Glass.

00:40:42.650 --> 00:40:46.690
So here's my shopping list for
Google I/O. I'm not sure that

00:40:46.690 --> 00:40:49.290
I got that last item, but I
did get the extra socks.

00:40:52.270 --> 00:40:56.590
Now on this Evernote note, if
I tap on that Share arrow, I

00:40:56.590 --> 00:41:00.470
get all the places I can
share this note to.

00:41:00.470 --> 00:41:03.550
And of course, I'm going
to tap on Glass to send

00:41:03.550 --> 00:41:06.520
this note to Glass.

00:41:06.520 --> 00:41:09.620
Now Evernote, since this is
primarily text, they do that

00:41:09.620 --> 00:41:12.245
thing where they insert a
Timeline item that's text, and

00:41:12.245 --> 00:41:14.500
it autopaginates.

00:41:14.500 --> 00:41:16.020
In this case, it's the
shopping list.

00:41:16.020 --> 00:41:17.530
It's simple, and it's easy.

00:41:17.530 --> 00:41:19.950
I can see it on Glass, so I can
go through the store and

00:41:19.950 --> 00:41:25.070
buy these extra socks or
unhealthy energy drinks

00:41:25.070 --> 00:41:27.280
without having to go back
and forth to my phone.

00:41:27.280 --> 00:41:28.530
It's a really cool experience.

00:41:33.930 --> 00:41:34.430
All right.

00:41:34.430 --> 00:41:36.550
Let's talk about Facebook.

00:41:36.550 --> 00:41:40.330
Facebook for Glass lets you
share your photos on Facebook.

00:41:40.330 --> 00:41:43.430
And you can choose who you want
to share with, and you

00:41:43.430 --> 00:41:45.240
can say something to
add a description.

00:41:45.240 --> 00:41:48.260
In this case, we've got
this photo that

00:41:48.260 --> 00:41:51.290
I've taken on Glass.

00:41:51.290 --> 00:41:55.750
Now I'm going to tap that image,
and I get options for

00:41:55.750 --> 00:41:58.770
Share and Delete.

00:41:58.770 --> 00:42:01.780
This is just, at this point,
a picture on Glass.

00:42:01.780 --> 00:42:03.630
When I tap on Share,
I get my whole

00:42:03.630 --> 00:42:05.670
list of sharing contacts.

00:42:05.670 --> 00:42:08.720
And one of them, once I've set
up the Facebook Glassware, is

00:42:08.720 --> 00:42:09.980
going to be much friends
on Facebook.

00:42:09.980 --> 00:42:13.900
Now you can also share with
public or with just yourself.

00:42:20.210 --> 00:42:23.160
I'm going to tap on this
sharing contact.

00:42:23.160 --> 00:42:26.610
And what Glass does is it
creates a new image on my

00:42:26.610 --> 00:42:28.570
Glass Timeline.

00:42:28.570 --> 00:42:31.510
This time it's owned by the
Facebook Glassware.

00:42:31.510 --> 00:42:35.410
They get a notification I tapped
on that Share target.

00:42:35.410 --> 00:42:37.530
And what Facebook is doing is
it's going back to that

00:42:37.530 --> 00:42:41.260
Timeline item and adding a new
menu item, Add Description.

00:42:41.260 --> 00:42:44.610
So this is immediately posted to
my Facebook Timeline, but I

00:42:44.610 --> 00:42:46.990
can tap here and add a
description, say these are

00:42:46.990 --> 00:42:49.810
white stargazers.

00:42:49.810 --> 00:42:53.410
And then Facebook will update
that Timeline item to also

00:42:53.410 --> 00:42:57.140
include that caption,
that description.

00:42:57.140 --> 00:42:59.870
And it updates the post
on Facebook as well.

00:43:04.090 --> 00:43:06.120
Now that picture is going to
show up on Facebook, so my

00:43:06.120 --> 00:43:08.165
Facebook friends can see it when
they visit my profile.

00:43:13.190 --> 00:43:17.250
This pattern here is the ability
to share a photo,

00:43:17.250 --> 00:43:19.210
delete it right away if
it's an oops moment.

00:43:19.210 --> 00:43:22.840
But then add a description
is really key.

00:43:22.840 --> 00:43:25.830
Because I can do all those
things with Glass and sort of

00:43:25.830 --> 00:43:27.880
just having that quick
experience or add a little bit

00:43:27.880 --> 00:43:29.050
more information to it.

00:43:29.050 --> 00:43:31.812
I really recommend
this pattern.

00:43:31.812 --> 00:43:32.220
All right.

00:43:32.220 --> 00:43:36.830
Let's talk about "Elle." Now I
am not the target consumer for

00:43:36.830 --> 00:43:43.210
"Elle." But what they're doing
with Glassware I think is just

00:43:43.210 --> 00:43:44.310
really cool.

00:43:44.310 --> 00:43:47.990
They also have this great
Settings page.

00:43:47.990 --> 00:43:51.580
And they're a really important,
maybe the number

00:43:51.580 --> 00:43:54.380
one, fashion magazine out there
in the world, part of

00:43:54.380 --> 00:43:57.630
the Hearst collection
of magazines.

00:43:57.630 --> 00:44:00.540
And it's a neat experience
on Glass.

00:44:00.540 --> 00:44:04.400
You can select on the Settings
page for all these different

00:44:04.400 --> 00:44:07.750
topics, much like
you do on CNN.

00:44:07.750 --> 00:44:09.400
But "Elle" does something
else that's

00:44:09.400 --> 00:44:11.290
really cool in the moment.

00:44:11.290 --> 00:44:16.110
As I get these items on Glass
throughout the day--

00:44:16.110 --> 00:44:18.100
and this is a bundle with
multiple pages--

00:44:22.900 --> 00:44:26.950
and I tap on any one of those
pages and I get this menu, I

00:44:26.950 --> 00:44:30.420
can have this read aloud, I can
share it, or right there

00:44:30.420 --> 00:44:32.110
in the middle I can add
to my reading list.

00:44:32.110 --> 00:44:37.050
Now I love this flow
for three reasons.

00:44:37.050 --> 00:44:40.490
First off, I think it's
cool for the user.

00:44:40.490 --> 00:44:45.140
As I'm reading "Elle" or other
articles on Glass, a lot of

00:44:45.140 --> 00:44:47.190
the time having that headline
or that little bit of

00:44:47.190 --> 00:44:49.260
information is exactly
what I wanted.

00:44:49.260 --> 00:44:50.950
I'm good.

00:44:50.950 --> 00:44:52.840
But sometimes it's like,
oh, I want to read

00:44:52.840 --> 00:44:54.010
more about this later.

00:44:54.010 --> 00:44:57.950
Or maybe I want to bring it up
on my computer at work on a

00:44:57.950 --> 00:45:00.770
big screen and share
it with my friends.

00:45:00.770 --> 00:45:01.680
How do I do that?

00:45:01.680 --> 00:45:05.130
Well, I tap on Reading List,
and "Elle" adds this to the

00:45:05.130 --> 00:45:07.190
Reading List on that Settings
page I showed you, right at

00:45:07.190 --> 00:45:08.400
the bottom.

00:45:08.400 --> 00:45:11.981
And it's all of the links that
I've saved throughout my day.

00:45:11.981 --> 00:45:14.380
So it's cool for the user.

00:45:14.380 --> 00:45:17.510
It also helps me, as a user,
spend more time with "Elle."

00:45:17.510 --> 00:45:20.040
because now I'm also on
their web product.

00:45:20.040 --> 00:45:23.250
And finally, it helps "Elle"
know what are some of the

00:45:23.250 --> 00:45:26.130
articles that I want to spend
more time with later, not just

00:45:26.130 --> 00:45:28.620
the updates throughout
the day.

00:45:28.620 --> 00:45:30.650
So it's really good for the
user, and I think it's really

00:45:30.650 --> 00:45:31.990
good for the brand.

00:45:34.720 --> 00:45:34.850
All right.

00:45:34.850 --> 00:45:36.755
I want to do one more example.

00:45:36.755 --> 00:45:38.320
And I love this story.

00:45:38.320 --> 00:45:41.770
Ice Breaker is here at Google
I/O. Whereas this isn't

00:45:41.770 --> 00:45:45.190
released on MyGlass website,
you can go to this website,

00:45:45.190 --> 00:45:47.720
and you can install it while
you're at I/O and play with

00:45:47.720 --> 00:45:48.220
each other.

00:45:48.220 --> 00:45:49.760
This is a game.

00:45:49.760 --> 00:45:51.880
A lot of what we've talked
about so far is very

00:45:51.880 --> 00:45:54.470
productive, and sharing
with friends, and

00:45:54.470 --> 00:45:55.410
it's a lot of fun.

00:45:55.410 --> 00:45:57.270
But also, I want to
have a whimsical

00:45:57.270 --> 00:45:59.270
experience with Glass.

00:45:59.270 --> 00:46:03.045
Now these three guys got
together at one of our Glass

00:46:03.045 --> 00:46:06.110
Foundry events, met each other,
built some awesome

00:46:06.110 --> 00:46:08.235
Glassware, and won
first prize.

00:46:08.235 --> 00:46:10.810
And afterwards, we were hanging
out, and we came up

00:46:10.810 --> 00:46:13.450
with this idea of Ice Breaker.

00:46:13.450 --> 00:46:15.110
And they built it
for Google I/O.

00:46:15.110 --> 00:46:16.490
This is what you do.

00:46:16.490 --> 00:46:20.830
You land on their page, the
icebreaker.io, and it's going

00:46:20.830 --> 00:46:21.950
to walk you through
the whole flow.

00:46:21.950 --> 00:46:25.220
But let me just touch
on what happens.

00:46:25.220 --> 00:46:26.800
First off, they send
a welcome card.

00:46:26.800 --> 00:46:28.030
And this is something
"Elle" does as well

00:46:28.030 --> 00:46:28.970
that I really like.

00:46:28.970 --> 00:46:30.830
When you sign up for the
Glassware, it immediately

00:46:30.830 --> 00:46:33.120
inserts a card into your
Timeline, so you know it all

00:46:33.120 --> 00:46:35.820
worked, and the user gets that
kind of warm, fuzzy feeling,

00:46:35.820 --> 00:46:38.020
like now I'm signed up
for Ice Breaker.

00:46:38.020 --> 00:46:39.310
And it tells you a little
bit about what's

00:46:39.310 --> 00:46:41.270
going to happen next.

00:46:41.270 --> 00:46:44.690
As Ice Breaker gets location
updates for where you are,

00:46:44.690 --> 00:46:49.230
it'll find somebody else also
playing Ice Breaker and sends

00:46:49.230 --> 00:46:53.330
you a card with their photo
and their name and the

00:46:53.330 --> 00:46:56.000
encouragement to go meet them
and have a conversation, or

00:46:56.000 --> 00:46:57.260
break the ice.

00:46:57.260 --> 00:47:00.350
You can get directions to this
person, you can pin or unpin

00:47:00.350 --> 00:47:03.335
this card, and you can
also give up if

00:47:03.335 --> 00:47:05.220
you can't find them.

00:47:05.220 --> 00:47:08.580
Now let's talk a little bit
about those last two items.

00:47:08.580 --> 00:47:12.125
First, the pinning, what this
does is when I pin a card,

00:47:12.125 --> 00:47:14.510
it's a System Menu item.

00:47:14.510 --> 00:47:15.910
It takes that card and
puts it on the

00:47:15.910 --> 00:47:17.840
left side of the Timeline.

00:47:17.840 --> 00:47:20.950
That's the space reserved for
things going on right now.

00:47:20.950 --> 00:47:22.190
Google Now is over there.

00:47:22.190 --> 00:47:24.450
You've got your weather card,
maybe some stocks that you're

00:47:24.450 --> 00:47:27.540
following, or other third party

00:47:27.540 --> 00:47:29.470
Glassware that you've pinned.

00:47:29.470 --> 00:47:31.410
In this case, I'm looking
for Jonathan.

00:47:31.410 --> 00:47:34.070
I want to make this new friend,
so I'm going to keep

00:47:34.070 --> 00:47:36.330
it pinned to the left side of me
Timeline so I can look back

00:47:36.330 --> 00:47:38.560
and like, OK, have
I found him yet?

00:47:38.560 --> 00:47:42.000
It's like a fun person
scavenger hunt.

00:47:42.000 --> 00:47:44.890
The third option there
is to give up.

00:47:44.890 --> 00:47:46.370
Glass is a very now device.

00:47:46.370 --> 00:47:47.360
Remember that?

00:47:47.360 --> 00:47:51.010
So in the patterns of doing
something with Glassware, like

00:47:51.010 --> 00:47:54.390
breaking the ice and finding
people to do that, what

00:47:54.390 --> 00:47:56.442
happens if I can't
find Jonathan?

00:47:56.442 --> 00:47:59.560
And in fact, Ice Breaker knows,
since it's getting

00:47:59.560 --> 00:48:02.260
location updates, if we get too
far away from each other,

00:48:02.260 --> 00:48:04.855
it'll send me a new person still
at the conference that I

00:48:04.855 --> 00:48:07.560
can find and make new
friends with.

00:48:07.560 --> 00:48:09.960
It's really cool, because it's
in the moment, and it matters

00:48:09.960 --> 00:48:12.610
to me right now.

00:48:12.610 --> 00:48:16.520
Now I find Jonathan, and
we have a conversation.

00:48:16.520 --> 00:48:19.360
We get to know each other, and
I take his picture, and I

00:48:19.360 --> 00:48:21.350
share it with Ice Breaker.

00:48:21.350 --> 00:48:23.450
He then gets a notification
being like, did

00:48:23.450 --> 00:48:24.460
Timothy really find you?

00:48:24.460 --> 00:48:26.025
And did you have a good
conversation?

00:48:26.025 --> 00:48:29.550
If the answer is yes, then
I get more points.

00:48:29.550 --> 00:48:32.660
And I keep looking to make new
friends who have Glass here at

00:48:32.660 --> 00:48:35.150
Google I/O. Again, I really
recommend you try this.

00:48:35.150 --> 00:48:36.400
It's a lot of fun.

